events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — The Boston Celtics were missing a lot of 3-point shots. They missed a bunch of layups, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 35, 17 in the fourth, to lead the Celtics to a 114-98 win over the Knicks

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored a season-high 39 points and the Toronto Raptors overcame a 23-point deficit to beat the Washington Wizards 111-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores season-high 39, Raptors overcome 23-point deficit to beat Wizards

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 35 points and 11 rebounds and Bobby Portis also had a double-double in the Milwaukee Bucks’ 118-109 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Portis produce double-doubles in Bucks' 118-109 victory over Bulls

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 28 points and six assists in his return after missing two weeks with an ankle injury, and the Sacramento Kings gave coach Mike Brown his 400th career victory with a 132-120 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De'Aaron Fox's return sparks Kings to 132-120 victory over Cavs as Mike Brown earns 400th win
